On February 27, 2010, the President signed two bills into law. The first bill, H.R. 3961, extends several terrorist surveillance provisions in the USA PATRIOT Act and the Intelligence Reform and Terrorism Prevention Act of 2004 for one year. The second bill, H.R. 4532, known as the "Social Security Disability Applicants' Access to Professional Representation Act of 2010," makes permanent the programs that allow direct payment of attorneys and certain non-attorney representatives in Social Security and Supplemental Security Income claims cases.